Program [/wiki/Wikipedia:Course_pages]Education Program\\\\\\\\ntalk4472300Gadget [/wiki/Wikipedia:Gadget]Gadget talk23012302Gadget definition\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Gadget]Gadget definition talk23032600Topic\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Flow]2601Virtual namespaces\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Namespace#Virtual_namespaces]-1Special\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Special_page]-2Media [/wiki/Help:Files]Current list\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:NamespaceInfo]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCategories are intended to group together pages on similar subjects. They are\\\\\\\\nimplemented by a MediaWiki [/wiki/MediaWiki] feature that adds any page with a\\\\\\\\ntext like [[Category:XYZ]] in its wiki markup to the automated listing that is\\\\\\\\nthe category with name XYZ. Categories help readers to find, and navigate\\\\\\\\naround, a subject area, to see pages sorted by title, and to thus find article\\\\\\\\nrelationships.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCategories are normally found at the bottom of an article page. Clicking a\\\\\\\\ncategory name brings up a category page listing the articles (or other pages)\\\\\\\\nthat have been added to that particular category. There may also be a section\\\\\\\\nlisting the subcategories of that category. The subcategorization feature makes\\\\\\\\nit possible to organize categories into tree-like structures to aid navigation.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe term category does refer to both the title of a category pagethe category\\\\\\\\npagenameand the category itself. Keeping this in mind while reading about\\\\\\\\ncategorization, plus learning a category page layout is a worthwhile investment\\\\\\\\nin research techniques. (See also the search box parameter \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"incategory\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/H:S#Parameters]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".) The layout of a category page is mostly text, but see\\\\\\\\nabout displaying category trees below.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSUMMARY\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe MediaWiki software maintains tables of categories, to which any editable\\\\\\\\npage can be added. To add a page to a category, include \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"[[Category:Category\\\\\\\\nname]]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"[[Category:Category name|Sortkey]]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in that page's wiki markup\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Wiki_markup]. The categories to which a page belongs appear in a box\\\\\\\\nat the bottom of the page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA category is usually associated with a category page in the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Category:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\nnamespace [/wiki/Wikipedia:Namespace].[1] A category page contains text that can\\\\\\\\nbe edited, like any other page, but when the page is displayed, the last part of\\\\\\\\nwhat is displayed is an automatically generated list of all pages in that\\\\\\\\ncategory, in the form of links. Other category pages which appear in this list\\\\\\\\nare treated separately, as subcategories.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Chicken_Eyeglasses_categories.png/960px-Chicken_Eyeglasses_categories.png]/wiki/File:Chicken_Eyeglasses_categories.pngThe\\\\\\\\nbottom of a Wikipedia article on Chicken eyeglasses [/wiki/Chicken_eyeglasses].\\\\\\\\nAt the very bottom of the page, below the References, navigation templates and\\\\\\\\nexternal links are a series of links. These links are the categories used on the\\\\\\\\npage, which include: Category:Animal welfare [/wiki/Category:Animal_welfare],\\\\\\\\nCategory:Animal equipment [/wiki/Category:Animal_equipment], Category:Eyewear\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Category:Eyewear], and Category:Poultry farming\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Category:Poultry_farming]. By clicking on the category link at the bottom\\\\\\\\nof the page, readers can navigate the Category tree.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCATEGORY PAGE DEFINITION\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA category page is any page in the Category namespace. They each act as a\\\\\\\\ncategory, and are termed a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"category\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". The category page has one section titled\\\\\\\\nSubcategories listing other \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"categories\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", and one section titled Pages, listing\\\\\\\\npages as categorized (in other namespaces). New categories are created by\\\\\\\\ncreating a page [/wiki/Wikipedia:How_to_create_a_page] in the Category\\\\\\\\nnamespace.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA category page can be edited like any other page. However, when it is\\\\\\\\ndisplayed, the editable part of the page is followed by automatically generated\\\\\\\\nlists of pages belonging to the category, as follows:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * First a count and list of subcategories (other categories belonging to the\\\\\\\\n   category) is shown, if any exist. The name of each subcategory is followed by\\\\\\\\n   counts like \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"(6 C, 38 P, 2 F)\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", meaning this subcategory contains 6\\\\\\\\n   subcategories, 38 pages, and 2 files. Counts of 0 are omitted. The further\\\\\\\\n   subcategories are expanded in the display if the  sign alongside the\\\\\\\\n   subcategory is clicked (the  is only visible if your browser has JavaScript\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/JavaScript] enabled). Note:  is shown if there are no further\\\\\\\\n   subcategories. The subcategory is collapsed again if  is clicked.\\\\\\\\n * Next a count and list of pages in the category (excluding subcategories and\\\\\\\\n   images) is shown. If the category has no members, a message to that effect is\\\\\\\\n   displayed.\\\\\\\\n * Next a count and list of image and other media files in the category appears,\\\\\\\\n   if any exist. These are shown with thumbnails. The first 20 characters of the\\\\\\\\n   file name are shown, with an ellipsis if that is not the full name; also the\\\\\\\\n   file size is shown.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe items in the lists all link to the pages concerned; in the case of the\\\\\\\\nimages this applies both to the image itself and to the text below it (the name\\\\\\\\nof the image).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor the way in which the lists are ordered, see Sorting category pages below.\\\\\\\\nThe first and second lists are divided into sections, according to the first\\\\\\\\ncharacter of the sort key. These initial characters are displayed above the\\\\\\\\nsections. To suppress these, make all sort keys start with a space.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA category page can only display a limited number of members (currently 200). If\\\\\\\\nthere are more members, there will be a link to the next page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe categories box for the category page appears at the bottom, in the same\\\\\\\\nplace as for other pages. This contains the categories to which the current\\\\\\\\ncategory page has been added, i.e., its parent categories (the categories of\\\\\\\\nwhich it is a subcategory). Add a category page to other categories in the\\\\\\\\nnormal way, using the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"[[Category:Category name]]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"[[Category:Category\\\\\\\\nname|Sortkey]]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" syntax.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPUTTING PAGES INTO CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nShortcut [/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut]\\\\\\\\n * WP:PAGECAT\\\\\\\\n   [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:PAGECAT&redirect=no]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSee also: Help:VisualEditor Editing categories\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:VisualEditor#Editing_categories]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA page becomes part of a category if the page's wiki markup contains a\\\\\\\\ndeclaration for that category. A category declaration takes the form\\\\\\\\n[[Category:Category name]] or [[Category:Category name|Sortkey]]. The\\\\\\\\ndeclaration must be processed, i.e. it will not work if it appears between\\\\\\\\n<nowiki>...</nowiki> or <includeonly>...</includeonly> tags, or in a comment.\\\\\\\\nThe declaration may however come from a transcluded\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Transclusion] page; see Categories and templates below.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA category name can be any string that would be a legitimate page title\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Page_title]. If the category name begins with a lower-case\\\\\\\\nletter, it will be capitalized. For initial lower-case letters, as in\\\\\\\\nCategory:macOS [/wiki/Category:MacOS], see the technical restrictions\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Naming_conventions_(technical_restrictions)#Lowercase_first_letter]\\\\\\\\npage.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOn Wikipedia, it is customary to place category declarations at the end of the\\\\\\\\nwiki markup, but before any stub [/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub] templates (which\\\\\\\\nthemselves transclude categories).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen a page has been added to one or more categories, a categories box appears\\\\\\\\nat the bottom of the page (or possibly elsewhere, if a non-default skin\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Skin] is being used). This box contains a list of the\\\\\\\\ncategories the page belongs to, in the order in which the category declarations\\\\\\\\nappear in the processed wiki markup. The category names are linked\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Link] to the corresponding category pages. They appear as red links\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Red_link] if the corresponding category page does not exist. If\\\\\\\\na user has enabled the HotCat [/wiki/Wikipedia:HOTCAT] gadget, the categories\\\\\\\\nbox will also provide links to quickly add, remove, or modify category\\\\\\\\ndeclarations on the page, without having to edit the whole page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHidden categories are not displayed, except as described below under Hiding\\\\\\\\ncategories.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWORKING WITH CATEGORY PAGES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe following subsections are ordered from simple actions to more elaborate or\\\\\\\\nrarer actions.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nLINKING TO CATEGORY PAGES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTo link to a category page without putting the current page in that category,\\\\\\\\nprecede the link with a colon: [[:Category:Category name]]. Such a link can be\\\\\\\\npiped [/wiki/Help:Piped_link] like a normal wikilink. (The {{cl\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Cl]}} template, and others listed on its documentation page, may\\\\\\\\nsometimes be helpful.)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRETRIEVING RAW CATEGORY INFORMATION\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRaw information about the members of a category, their sort keys and timestamps\\\\\\\\n(time when last added to the category) can be obtained from the API\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/API], using a query of the form:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?cmtitle=Category:Category_name&action=query&list=categorymembers&cmlimit=500&cmprop=title|sortkey|timestamp\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nListings of up to 500 members are possible. If there are more members then the\\\\\\\\nresults will include text near the end like this: <categorymembers\\\\\\\\ncmcontinue=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"page|NNNN|TITLE\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" />.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis can be added to the previous one, without quotation marks, for the next\\\\\\\\npage of members: ...&cmcontinue=page|NNNN|TITLE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSORTING CATEGORY PAGES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nShortcut [/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut]\\\\\\\\n * WP:SORTCAT\\\\\\\\n   [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:SORTCAT&redirect=no]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBy default, a page is sorted under the first character of its name, without the\\\\\\\\nnamespace. English Wikipedia groups accented characters together with their\\\\\\\\nunaccented version, so pages starting with , , , will be listed under heading\\\\\\\\nA. Sorting is case-insensitive, so \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"ABC\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" comes after \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Abacus\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUnlike at Special:Allpages [/wiki/Special:AllPages] and Special:Prefixindex\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:PrefixIndex], a space is treated as a space (coming before all\\\\\\\\nother characters), not as an underscore.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe English Wikipedia has numerical sorting in categories\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Manual:$wgCategoryCollation#Numeric_sorting].\\\\\\\\nThis means that digit sequences in page names are treated according to their\\\\\\\\nnumerical value, not as strings. Thus \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"9 dogs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"25 dogs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", and \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"112 dogs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" will\\\\\\\\nall appear under the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"09\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" heading in numerical order, and V838 Monocerotis\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/V838_Monocerotis] will appear before V1309 Scorpii [/wiki/V1309_Scorpii].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEach of the three lists (subcategories, pages, media files) is arranged in the\\\\\\\\norder explained above (except that, in the subcategories list, the namespace\\\\\\\\nindicator \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Category:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" is not considered). If an item ought to be positioned\\\\\\\\nwithin a list on the basis of an alternative name (sort key) for that item, then\\\\\\\\nthis can be specified in the category tag that places the item in the list:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[[Category:Category name|Sortkey]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor example, to add an article called Albert Einstein [/wiki/Albert_Einstein] to\\\\\\\\nCategory:1879 births [/wiki/Category:1879_births] and have the article sorted by\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Einstein, Albert\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", you would type:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[[Category:1879 births|Einstein, Albert]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUnlike a piped link [/wiki/Help:Piped_link] (which uses the same syntax), the\\\\\\\\nsort key itself is not displayed to readers. It affects only the order in which\\\\\\\\npages are listed on the category page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt is useful to document the system being used for sort keys on the category\\\\\\\\npage. For guidelines about the use of sort keys on Wikipedia, see WP:SORTKEY\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:SORTKEY].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDEFAULT SORT KEY\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nShortcut [/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut]\\\\\\\\n * WP:DEFAULTSORT\\\\\\\\n   [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:DEFAULTSORT&redirect=no]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis section documents functionality. For guidelines, see WP:NAMESORT\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:NAMESORT] and WP:SORTKEY [/wiki/Wikipedia:SORTKEY].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt is possible to set a default sort key which is different from {{PAGENAME}} by\\\\\\\\nusing the magic word [/wiki/Help:Magic_words#Behavior_switches]\\\\\\\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:}}:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:new key}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is often used in biography articles, to make sure the subject is sorted by\\\\\\\\ntheir last name:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:LastName, FirstName}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor example, on the Albert Einstein [/wiki/Albert_Einstein] page,\\\\\\\\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Einstein, Albert}} adds the sort key \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Einstein, Albert\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" to all his\\\\\\\\ncategories, such as Category:1879 births [/wiki/Category:1879_births].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn the case of multiple default sort key tags, the last DEFAULTSORT on the final\\\\\\\\nrendering of a page applies for all categories, regardless of the position of\\\\\\\\nthe category tags. This also means that a DEFAULTSORT tag included from a\\\\\\\\ntemplate is not effective if another DEFAULTSORT tag occurs later on the page,\\\\\\\\neven if the later DEFAULTSORT tag is also \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"hidden\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (included by another\\\\\\\\ntemplate).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSEARCHING FOR PAGES IN CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFurther information: Help:Searching Syntax [/wiki/Help:Searching#Syntax]\\\\\\\\nSee also: Wikipedia:Category intersection\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Category_intersection]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn addition to browsing through hierarchies of categories, it is possible to use\\\\\\\\nthe search tool to find specific articles in specific categories. To search for\\\\\\\\narticles in a specific category, type incategory:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"CategoryName\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in the search\\\\\\\\nbox.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA pipe \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"|\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" can be added to join the contents of one category with the contents\\\\\\\\nof another. For example, enter\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nincategory:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Suspension bridges|Bridges in New York City\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nto return all pages that belong to either (or both) of the categories, as here\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Search&search=incategory%3A%22Suspension+bridges%7CBridges+in+New+York+City%22&ns0=1&fulltext=Search].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNote that using search to find categories will not find articles which have been\\\\\\\\ncategorized using templates. This feature also doesn't return pages in\\\\\\\\nsubcategories.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nLISTING ALL CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSpecial:Categories [/wiki/Special:Categories] provides an alphabetic list of all\\\\\\\\ncategories, with the number of members of each; this number does not include the\\\\\\\\ncontent of the subcategories, but it includes the subcategories themselves,\\\\\\\\ni.e., each counting as one.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe above list contains all categories that have members, regardless of whether\\\\\\\\nthey have corresponding category pages. To list all existing category pages\\\\\\\\n(regardless of whether they have members), use Special:AllPages/Category:\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:AllPages/Category:].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDISPLAYING CATEGORY TREES AND PAGE COUNTS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAs described at mw:Help:Magic words\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Magic_words], {{PAGESINCATEGORY:Example}}\\\\\\\\nor {{PAGESINCAT:Example}} returns the number of pages in \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Category:Example\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\nEach subcategory counts as one page; pages in subcategories are not counted.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe page Special:CategoryTree [/wiki/Special:CategoryTree] enables you to see\\\\\\\\nthe tree structure of a category (its subcategories, their subcategories and so\\\\\\\\non; the display of files and other member pages is optional).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe CategoryTree extension\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:CategoryTree] can be used to display\\\\\\\\nsuch a tree on any page. (This is sometimes done on the category page itself, if\\\\\\\\nthe category is split over multiple screens, to make all subcategories available\\\\\\\\non every screen.) The basic syntax is\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * <categorytree>Category name</categorytree>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nto display just the subcategory tree, and\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * <categorytree mode=pages>Category name</categorytree>\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nto display member pages as well. They will be indicated by italics.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDapete's [/wiki/User:Dapete] category-visualizer vCat\\\\\\\\n[https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/User:Dapete/vCat#English] will render charts of\\\\\\\\nthe tree structure.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou may also use Template:Category tree [/wiki/Template:Category_tree] or\\\\\\\\nTemplate:Category tree all [/wiki/Template:Category_tree_all], instead.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWarning:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe following code {{PAGESINCATEGORY:{{PAGENAME}}}} will not work as expected\\\\\\\\nwhen used in the wikitext or in a transcluded template in a category page whose\\\\\\\\ntitle contains some ASCII punctuations.For legacy reasons, {{PAGENAME}} may\\\\\\\\nreturn the page name with these characters being HTML-encoded using numeric\\\\\\\\ncharacter entities: this still works for generating derived wikilinks or\\\\\\\\ndisplaying page names, or when HTML-encoded this page name is used in a\\\\\\\\nconditional \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"#switch\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", but PAGESINCATEGORY does not recognize the category name\\\\\\\\ngiven in parameter if some characters are HTML-encoded (this is the case notably\\\\\\\\nwhen the category name contains ASCII apostrophes ' and a few other ASCII\\\\\\\\npunctuations. (The same HTML-encoding is also applied to the values returned by\\\\\\\\n{{FULLPAGENAME}}, {{SUBPAGENAME}}, or {{NAMESPACE}}).In that case, as the\\\\\\\\ncategory is not found by its HTML-encoded pagename, PAGESINCATEGORY will\\\\\\\\nunexpectedly return 0 and not its effective number of member pages.A simple\\\\\\\\nworkaround is to transform these HTML-encoded characters back into standard\\\\\\\\nUTF-8-encoded characters, by using the {{titleparts:}} parser function, like\\\\\\\\nthis:{{PAGESINCATEGORY:{{titleparts:{{PAGENAME}}}}}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMOVING AND REDIRECTING CATEGORY PAGES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCategories can be moved [/wiki/Help:Moving_a_page#How_to_move_a_category] in the\\\\\\\\nsame way as an ordinary page; but a certain amount of cleanup may be necessary.\\\\\\\\nA redirect is left at the old category name, and this is not a normal\\\\\\\\n#REDIRECT[[...]] but a {{category redirect\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Category_redirect]}}. Once all the pages have been moved out of\\\\\\\\nthe old category, it may be left as a category redirect or deleted. For\\\\\\\\ncategories entirely populated through templates (see above), modifying the\\\\\\\\ntemplates enables all affected articles to be moved to another category, but\\\\\\\\nwith the refresh problem mentioned. Almost all category name changes are made\\\\\\\\npursuant to a consensus decision at Wikipedia:Categories for discussion\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Categories_for_discussion].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDo not create intercategory redirects other than with a {{category redirect\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Category_redirect]}} template. See Wikipedia:Categories for\\\\\\\\ndiscussion Redirecting categories\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Categories_for_discussion#Redirecting_categories] for more on\\\\\\\\ncategory redirects.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHIDING CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhen the magic word [/wiki/Help:Magic_words] __HIDDENCAT__ is placed on a\\\\\\\\ncategory page, that category becomes hidden, meaning that it will not be\\\\\\\\ndisplayed on the pages belonging to that category. On Wikipedia, the magic word\\\\\\\\nis not normally used explicitly, but is applied through the {{hidden category\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Hidden_category]}} template. The feature is mostly used to\\\\\\\\nprevent project maintenance categories from showing up to ordinary readers on\\\\\\\\narticle pages.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor users who are not logged in [/wiki/Help:Logging_in], hidden categories are\\\\\\\\ndisplayed on category pages (whether as parent categories or subcategories).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHidden categories are displayed at the bottom of each page, after \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Hidden\\\\\\\\ncategories:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", for registered users:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * at preview during editing;\\\\\\\\n * if the user has selected \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Show hidden categories\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in their user preferences.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHidden categories are automatically added to Category:Hidden categories\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Category:Hidden_categories].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor guidelines on the hiding of categories on Wikipedia, see WP:HIDDENCAT\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:HIDDENCAT].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTRACKING CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTracking categories are used to track technical featues or problems. They are\\\\\\\\noutside of the category structure for articles. Pages may be inserted into those\\\\\\\\nby the MediaWiki software, or by templates or modules. Usually they are hidden,\\\\\\\\nor even red ie not created. Special:TrackingCategories\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:TrackingCategories] lists all tracking categories populated by\\\\\\\\nthe MediaWiki software. Category:Tracking categories\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Category:Tracking_categories] is the top for tracking categories on this\\\\\\\\nwiki.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFINDING ARTICLES FOR A CATEGORY\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe most effective way of finding entries of a category is using the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"What links\\\\\\\\nhere [/wiki/Help:What_links_here]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" tool on the category's main article.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAn easy way to find relevant articles for a new category or missing entries in\\\\\\\\nan existing one is by finding the most relevant list [/wiki/Help:List] and\\\\\\\\nchecking its entries. Sometimes categories are about things that are\\\\\\\\nintersections of other categories [/wiki/Wikipedia:Category_intersection] for\\\\\\\\nwhich the PetScan tool [https://petscan.wmflabs.org/] can be used.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMore relevant articles may also be found linked in a category's main article and\\\\\\\\nthe articles already featured in the category  especially in their \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"See also\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:ALSO] sections (if existent) and the automatically suggested\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"RELATED ARTICLES\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" below them.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFurthermore, a category's superordinate categories often feature articles that\\\\\\\\nshould be subcategorized to the category.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOther ways to find relevant articles include searching Wikipedia\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:Search] for the category's topic and searching the Web for the\\\\\\\\ntopic in quotes \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (with synonyms also in quotes and appended after an OR) and\\\\\\\\nappending the word wiki or Wikipedia or site:Wikipedia.org to them.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCATEGORIZING\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMain page: Wikipedia:Categorization [/wiki/Wikipedia:Categorization]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCATEGORIZING TEMPLATES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTemplates are categorized the same way as articles, except that [[Category:\\\\\\\\nSome-topic templates]] should be placed on the template's documentation page (or\\\\\\\\ninside <noinclude>...</noinclude> tags, if there is no documentation page), this\\\\\\\\nis necessary to avoid categorizing pages by template inclusion (see below).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCATEGORIES AND TEMPLATES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA template can be used to add pages to a category, usually by placing the\\\\\\\\ncategory link inside <includeonly></includeonly> tags on the template (e.g.\\\\\\\\n<includeonly>[[Category:category name]]</includeonly>). When the template is\\\\\\\\ntranscluded into the page, the category link becomes active, and the page is\\\\\\\\nadded to the category page. This is useful for categories that have high\\\\\\\\nturnover or many pages included, like cleanup categories.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nChanges to the template, however, may not be reflected immediately on the\\\\\\\\ncategory page. When you edit an article to add a category tag directly, the list\\\\\\\\nof category members is updated immediately when the page is saved. When a\\\\\\\\ncategory link is contained in a template, however, this does not happen\\\\\\\\nimmediately: instead, whenever a template is edited, all the pages that\\\\\\\\ntransclude it are put into the job queue [/wiki/Help:Job_queue] to be recached\\\\\\\\nduring periods of low server load. This means that, in busy periods, it may take\\\\\\\\nhours or even days before individual pages are recached and they start to appear\\\\\\\\nin the category list. Performing a null edit [/wiki/Help:Null_edit] to a page\\\\\\\\nwill allow it to jump the queue and be immediately recached.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTo add the template itself to the category page as well, omit the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"includeonly\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\ntags. To add the template to a category without categorizing pages on which the\\\\\\\\ntemplate is transcluded, place the category declaration between\\\\\\\\n<noinclude>...</noinclude> tags, or add it to the template documentation\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Template_documentation] page between\\\\\\\\n<includeonly></includeonly> (the latter allows recategorizing the template\\\\\\\\nwithout editing it, which is helpful if it is protected, or so complicated that\\\\\\\\nmere mortals hesitate to touch it).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nParser functions [/wiki/Help:Parser_function] can be used to make the\\\\\\\\ntranscluded categories, or the sort key used in them, dependent on other\\\\\\\\nvariables, notably PAGENAME.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPassing a category name as a\\\\\\\\nparameter<includeonly>[[Category:{{{cat|default}}}]]</includeonly> or\\\\\\\\n<includeonly>{{{cat|[[Category:default]]}}}</includeonly>\\\\\\\\nIf the user provides a parameter 'cat=XXX' the page will be categorized at the\\\\\\\\npage [[Category:XXX]], otherwise it will be categorized at the page\\\\\\\\n[[Category:default]]. Calling the template with \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"cat=\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" (equal to nothing)\\\\\\\\ndisables putting the page in any category.Excluding non-article\\\\\\\\npages<includeonly>{{#if:{{NAMESPACE}} | | [[Category:XXX]]}}</includeonly>\\\\\\\\nthe variable NAMESPACE is null for mainspace articles. For any space other than\\\\\\\\nmainspace, this ParserFunction will produce an empty string, but for regular\\\\\\\\narticles this will include the article in Category:XXX.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOn Wikipedia it is not recommended that templates be used to populate ordinary\\\\\\\\ncontent categories of articles. See Categorization using templates\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Categorization#Categorization_using_templates] in the\\\\\\\\ncategorization guideline.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCATEGORIZING REDIRECT PAGES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMain page: Wikipedia:Categorizing redirects\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Categorizing_redirects]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRedirect pages can be categorized and there are conventions on how to do it. The\\\\\\\\nredirect link must be first on the page. On a category page, redirects are\\\\\\\\nlisted in italics.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"RELATED CHANGES\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" WITH CATEGORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor a category, the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Related Changes [/wiki/Help:Related_changes]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" feature, when\\\\\\\\napplied to the corresponding category page, lists recent changes to the pages\\\\\\\\nwhich are currently listed as belonging to a category. Where those pages are\\\\\\\\nsubcategories or image pages, only changes to their editable parts are listed.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNotice that \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Related Changes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" does not show edits to pages that have been\\\\\\\\nremoved from the category.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAlso, \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Related Changes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" does not list recent changes to pages linked from the\\\\\\\\neditable part of the category page (as it would normally, with a non-category\\\\\\\\npage). If a workaround would be required, the links in question could be placed\\\\\\\\nin a template and transcluded onto the category page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAs usual  unlike with watchlists [/wiki/Help:Watchlist]  recent changes to\\\\\\\\ncorresponding talk pages [/wiki/Help:Talk_page] are not shown under \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Related\\\\\\\\nChanges\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". Pages that one is watching are bolded on the list. This can help to\\\\\\\\nfind which pages in a given category one has on one's watchlist.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe DynamicPageList (third-party)\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:DynamicPageList_(third-party)]\\\\\\\\nextension provides a list of last edits to the pages in a category, or\\\\\\\\noptionally, just the list of pages; the simpler DynamicPageList (Wikimedia)\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:DynamicPageList_(Wikimedia)] is\\\\\\\\ninstalled on Meta, Wikinews, Wikibooks\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Template:RC] and Wikiversity; the extension\\\\\\\\nmw:Extension:DPLforum [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:DPLforum] is\\\\\\\\ninstalled on Wikia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWATCHING CATEGORY ADDITIONS AND REMOVALS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSince 2016 [https://phabricator.wikimedia.org/T9148], additions and removals\\\\\\\\nfrom categories are available via the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Category changes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" filter\\\\\\\\n[https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:New_filters_for_edit_review/Filtering#Type_of_change]\\\\\\\\non recent changes pages, including watchlists [/wiki/Help:Watchlist] and\\\\\\\\nSpecial:RecentChangesLinked [/wiki/Special:RecentChangesLinked]. For example,\\\\\\\\ncategory changes to articles in Category:Cannabis stubs\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Category:Cannabis_stubs] can be found here\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChangesLinked&hidepageedits=1&hidenewpages=1&hideWikibase=1&hidelog=1&target=Category%3ACannabis_stubs&days=30&urlversion=2].\\\\\\\\nYou can monitor additions and removals from specific categories by adding the\\\\\\\\ncategories to your watchlist and making sure the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Category changes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" filter is\\\\\\\\nactive. You can view changes to categories in your watchlist by clicking here\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Watchlist&hidemyself=1&hidepageedits=1&hidenewpages=1&hideWikibase=1&hidelog=1&days=30&urlversion=2].\\\\\\\\nAdditional scripts with similar functionality are User:CategoryWatchlistBot\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/User:CategoryWatchlistBot] and User:Ais523/catwatch\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/User:Ais523/catwatch].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSEE ALSO\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * MediaWiki: Help:Categories [https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Help:Categories]\\\\\\\\n * Template:Category TOC [/wiki/Template:Category_TOC]\\\\\\\\n * Wikipedia:FAQ/Categorization [/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ/Categorization]\\\\\\\\n * Wikipedia:WikiProject Categories [/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Categories]\\\\\\\\n * Wikipedia:Quick cat index [/wiki/Wikipedia:Quick_cat_index]\\\\\\\\n * How to move a category [/wiki/Wikipedia:Moving_a_page#How_to_move_a_category]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNOTES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n 1. ^ The category itself is permanently created as soon as it has been saved on\\\\\\\\n    to any page. Unless you create a category page, it will display as a red\\\\\\\\n    link. Unless you add another category to the category page, it will not be\\\\\\\\n    placed in the category tree. Category pages are created like any other page.\\\\\\\\n    Most commonly, editors click on the redlink in an article and create the\\\\\\\\n    category page that way.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * v [/wiki/Template:Wikipedia_help_pages]\\\\\\\\n * t [/wiki/Template_talk:Wikipedia_help_pages]\\\\\\\\n * e [/wiki/Special:EditPage/Template:Wikipedia_help_pages]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWikipedia help pages [/wiki/Help:Directory]\\\\\\\\n * Visit the Teahouse [/wiki/Wikipedia:Teahouse] or the Help desk\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Wikipedia:Help_desk] for an interactive Q & A forum.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * FAQs [/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ](?)\\\\\\\\n * Reference desks [/wiki/Wikipedia:Reference_desk](?)\\\\\\\\n * Noticeboards [/wiki/Wikipedia:Noticeboards](?)\\\\\\\\n * Cheatsheet [/wiki/Help:Cheatsheet](?)\\\\\\\\n * Directories [/wiki/Wikipedia:Directories_and_indexes](?)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAbout Wikipedia [/wiki/Wikipedia:About](?)\\\\\\\\n * Administration [/wiki/Wikipedia:Administration]\\\\\\\\n   * Purpose [/wiki/Wikipedia:Purpose]\\\\\\\\n   * Principles [/wiki/Wikipedia:Five_pillars]\\\\\\\\n * Policies and guidelines [/wiki/Wikipedia:Policies_and_guidelines]\\\\\\\\n * What Wikipedia is not [/wiki/Wikipedia:What_Wikipedia_is_not]\\\\\\\\n * Disclaimer [/wiki/Wikipedia:General_disclaimer](parental advice\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Wikipedia:Advice_for_parents])\\\\\\\\n * Making requests [/wiki/Wikipedia:Request_directory]\\\\\\\\n * Who writes Wikipedia? desk\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/QA_icon.svg/40px-QA_icon.svg.png]/wiki/Wikipedia:Help_desk\\\\\\\\nPage semi-protected\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1b/Semi-protection-shackle.svg/20px-Semi-protection-shackle.svg.png]/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#semi\\\\\\\\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMain page of the help namespace\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis page provides help with the most common questions about Wikipedia\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou can also search Wikipedia's help pages using the search box below, or browse\\\\\\\\nthe Help menu [/wiki/Help:Menu] or the Help directory [/wiki/Help:Directory].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHelp Wikipedia\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c4/OOjs_UI_icon_article-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_article-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nREAD OR FIND AN ARTICLE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe Readers' FAQ [/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ/Readers] and our about page\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:About] contain the most commonly sought information about\\\\\\\\nWikipedia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor simple searches, there is a search bar at the top of every page. Type what\\\\\\\\nyou are looking for in the box. Suggested matches will appear in a dropdown\\\\\\\\nlist. Select any page in the list to go to that page. Or, select the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Search\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\nbutton, or press  Enter, to go to a full search result. For advanced searches,\\\\\\\\nsee Help:Searching [/wiki/Help:Searching].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThere are other ways to browse and explore Wikipedia articles; many can be found\\\\\\\\nat Wikipedia:Contents [/wiki/Wikipedia:Contents]. See our disclaimer\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:General_disclaimer] for cautions about Wikipedia's limitations.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor mobile access [/wiki/Help:Mobile_access], press the mobile view\\\\\\\\n[https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Contents] link at the very bottom of every\\\\\\\\ndesktop view [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Contents] page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/OOjs_UI_icon_edit-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_edit-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEDIT AN ARTICLE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nContributing is easy: see how to edit a page [/wiki/Help:Editing]. For a quick\\\\\\\\nsummary on participating, see contributing to Wikipedia\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Contributing_to_Wikipedia], and for a friendly tutorial, see\\\\\\\\nour introduction [/wiki/Help:Introduction]. For a listing of introductions and\\\\\\\\ntutorials by topic, see getting started [/wiki/Help:Getting_started]. The\\\\\\\\nSimplified Manual of Style [/wiki/Wikipedia:SMOS] and Cheatsheet\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Cheatsheet] can remind you of basic wiki markup\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Wikitext].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBebold [/wiki/Wikipedia:Be_bold] in improving articles! When adding facts,\\\\\\\\nplease provide references [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing/1] so others\\\\\\\\nmay verify them. If you are affiliated with the article subject, please see our\\\\\\\\nconflict of interest guideline [/wiki/Wikipedia:Conflict_of_interest].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe simple guide to vandalism cleanup\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Simple_guide_to_vandalism_cleanup] can help you undo malicious\\\\\\\\nedits.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you're looking for places you can help out, the Task Center\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Task_Center] is the place to go, or check out what else is\\\\\\\\nhappening at the community portal [/wiki/Wikipedia:Community_portal]. You can\\\\\\\\npractice editing and experiment in a sandbox [/wiki/Wikipedia:Sandbox]your\\\\\\\\nsandbox [/wiki/Special:MyPage/sandbox].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/OOjs_UI_icon_bell.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_bell.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nREPORT A PROBLEM WITH AN ARTICLE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf there is a problem with an article about yourself, a family member, a friend\\\\\\\\nor a colleague, please read Biographies of living persons/Help\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Biographies_of_living_persons/Help].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you spot a problem with an article, you can fix it directly, by clicking on\\\\\\\\nthe \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Edit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" link at the top of that page. See the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"edit an article\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" section of\\\\\\\\nthis page for more information.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you don't feel ready to fix the article yourself, post a message on the\\\\\\\\narticle's talk page [/wiki/Wikipedia:Talk_page_guidelines]. This will bring the\\\\\\\\nmatter to the attention of others who work on that article. There is a \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Talk\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\nlink at the beginning of every article page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou can contact us [/wiki/Wikipedia:Contact_us_-_Readers]. If it's an article\\\\\\\\nabout you or your organization, see Contact us  Subjects\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Contact_us_-_Subjects].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/06/OOjs_UI_icon_add.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_add.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCREATE A NEW ARTICLE OR UPLOAD MEDIA\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCheck Your first article [/wiki/Wikipedia:Your_first_article] to see if your\\\\\\\\ntopic is appropriate, then the Article wizard [/wiki/Wikipedia:Article_wizard]\\\\\\\\nwill walk you through creating the article.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOnce you have created an article, see Writing better articles\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Writing_better_articles] for guidance on how to improve it and\\\\\\\\nwhat to include (like reference citations [/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources]).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor contributing images, audio or video files, see the Introduction to uploading\\\\\\\\nimages [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_uploading_images/1]. Then the Upload wizard\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:File_Upload_Wizard] will guide you through that process.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/OOjs_UI_icon_help.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_help.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFAQ AND INTERACTIVE HELP\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAnswers to common problems can be found at frequently asked questions\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOr check out where to ask questions or make comments\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Questions].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNew users should seek help at the Teahouse [/wiki/Wikipedia:Teahouse] if they're\\\\\\\\nhaving problems while editing Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMore complex questions can be posed at the Help desk\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Help_desk]. Volunteers will respond as soon as they're able.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOr ask for help on your talk page\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:MyTalk&action=edit&section=new&preload=Help:Contents/helpmepreload&preloadtitle=Help+me%21]\\\\\\\\nand a volunteer will visit you there!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou can get live help with editing in the help chatroom\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:IRC_help_disclaimer].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor help with technical issues, ask at the Village pump\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Village_pump_(technical)].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/60/OOjs_UI_icon_references-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_references-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFACTUAL QUESTIONS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf searching Wikipedia [/wiki/Special:Search] has not answered your question\\\\\\\\n(for example, questions like \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Which country has the world's largest fishing\\\\\\\\nfleet?\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), try the Reference Desk [/wiki/Wikipedia:Reference_desk]. Volunteers\\\\\\\\nthere will attempt to answer your questions on any topic, or point you toward\\\\\\\\nthe information you need.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/OOjs_UI_icon_listBullet-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_listBullet-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDIRECTORIES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:Directory]: main list of directories and indexes.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHELP RELATED\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Help directory [/wiki/Help:Directory]: for informative, instructional and\\\\\\\\n   consultation pages.\\\\\\\\n * Request directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:Request_directory]: for services and\\\\\\\\n   assistance that can be requested on Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPROTOCOLS AND CONVENTIONS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Policy directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:List_of_policies]: official policies for\\\\\\\\n   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"English Wikipedia\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n * Guideline directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:List_of_guidelines]: official guidelines\\\\\\\\n   for \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"English Wikipedia\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n * Manual of Style directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style/Contents]: pages\\\\\\\\n   related to the style manual of Wikipedia articles.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCOMMUNITY RELATED\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Departments [/wiki/Wikipedia:Department_directory]: for the different\\\\\\\\n   divisions of Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n * Editor's index [/wiki/Wikipedia:Editor%27s_index_to_Wikipedia]: for\\\\\\\\n   everything an editor needs to know to work on Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n * Essay directory [/wiki/Wikipedia:Essay_directory]: for Wikipedia namespace\\\\\\\\n   essays.\\\\\\\\n * Dashboard [/wiki/Wikipedia:Dashboard]: for current discussions taking place\\\\\\\\n   throughout Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n * WikiProjects [/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Council/Directory]: for people who\\\\\\\\n   want to work together as a team to improve Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMEDIAWIKI SOFTWARE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Wikitext [/wiki/Help:Wikitext]: for the syntax used by Wikipedia to format a\\\\\\\\n   page.\\\\\\\\n * HTML [/wiki/Help:HTML_in_wikitext]: for HTML5 elements, or tags and their\\\\\\\\n   attribute.\\\\\\\\n * Templates [/wiki/Wikipedia:Template_index]: for templates used within\\\\\\\\n   Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b2/OOjs_UI_icon_listBullet-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_listBullet-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHELP BY TOPIC\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Help Menu [/wiki/Help:Menu]: for searching by subject matter.\\\\\\\\n * Navigating Wikipedia [/wiki/Help:Menu/Navigating_Wikipedia]: for searching\\\\\\\\n   and browsing the encyclopedia.\\\\\\\\n * Joining Wikipedia [/wiki/Help:Menu/Joining_Wikipedia]: how to get involved.\\\\\\\\n * Editing Wikipedia [/wiki/Help:Menu/Editing_Wikipedia]: has general help for\\\\\\\\n   editors.\\\\\\\\n * Links and references [/wiki/Help:Menu/Links]: has help for creating links, or\\\\\\\\n   dealing with references\\\\\\\\n * Images and media [/wiki/Help:Menu/Images_and_media]: how to use images,\\\\\\\\n   videos and sound files.\\\\\\\\n * Keeping track of changes [/wiki/Help:Menu/Tracking_changes]: how to track the\\\\\\\\n   evolution of a page, or follow a user.\\\\\\\\n * Policies and guidelines [/wiki/Help:Menu/Policies_and_guidelines]: for\\\\\\\\n   community standards.\\\\\\\\n * Asking questions [/wiki/Help:Menu/Asking_questions]: volunteers will attempt\\\\\\\\n   to answer.\\\\\\\\n * The Wikipedia community [/wiki/Help:Menu/The_Wikipedia_community]: how to\\\\\\\\n   submit or debate a proposal.\\\\\\\\n * Resources and lists [/wiki/Help:Menu/Resources_and_lists]: has resources for\\\\\\\\n   editors.\\\\\\\\n * Account settings [/wiki/Help:Menu/Account_settings_and_maintenance]: has tips\\\\\\\\n   and tools for registered users.\\\\\\\\n * Technical information [/wiki/Help:Menu/Technical_information]: has tools for\\\\\\\\n   advanced users, and troubleshooting.\\\\\\\\n * Site map [/wiki/Help:Menu/Site_map]: is the above thirteen pages on one\\\\\\\\n   single page.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/OOjs_UI_icon_lightbulb.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_lightbulb.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTIP OF THE DAY\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCollaborations\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA collaboration is when users work together to improve an article toward\\\\\\\\nfeatured [/wiki/Wikipedia:Featured_articles] status. They can work on almost any\\\\\\\\nsubject there is. These are usually run by the wikiprojects\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject] that work on articles in that area. Everyone is\\\\\\\\ninvited to work on the collaboration of their choice.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPrior tip [/wiki/Wikipedia:Tip_of_the_day/April_7]Tips library\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Tips]Next tip [/wiki/Wikipedia:Tip_of_the_day/April_9]\\\\\\\\nRead more:\\\\\\\\nWikipedia:Collaborations [/wiki/Wikipedia:Collaborations]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBecome a Wikipedia tipster [/wiki/Wikipedia:Wikipedia_tipster]  Tips library,\\\\\\\\nby subject [/wiki/Wikipedia:Tips]\\\\\\\\nTo add this auto-updating daily tip to your user page, use {{totd\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Totd]}}\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/de/OOjs_UI_icon_search-ltr.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_search-ltr.svg.png]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nADDITIONAL SEARCHES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSearch Frequently Asked Questions [/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSearch the help desk archives [/wiki/Wikipedia:Help_desk/Archives]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * v [/wiki/Template:Basic_information]\\\\\\\\n * t [/wiki/Template_talk:Basic_information]\\\\\\\\n * e [/wiki/Special:EditPage/Template:Basic_information]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBasic information on Wikipedia [/wiki/Category:Wikipedia_basic_information] -\\\\\\\\n(Search [/wiki/Help:Searching#Custom_search_boxes])\\\\\\\\n * Help\\\\\\\\n   * directory [/wiki/Help:Directory]\\\\\\\\n   * menu [/wiki/Help:Menu]\\\\\\\\n * Teahouse [/wiki/Wikipedia:Teahouse] (interactive help for new editors)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAbout Wikipedia [/wiki/Wikipedia:About]\\\\\\\\n * Readers' index to Wikipedia [/wiki/Wikipedia:Reader%27s_index_to_Wikipedia]\\\\\\\\n * Statistics [/wiki/Wikipedia:Statistics]\\\\\\\\n * Administration [/wiki/Wikipedia:Administration]\\\\\\\\n * FAQs [/wiki/Wikipedia:FAQ/Index]\\\\\\\\n   * Purpose [/wiki/Wikipedia:Purpose]\\\\\\\\n   * Who writes Wikipedia? semi-protected\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1b/Semi-protection-shackle.svg/20px-Semi-protection-shackle.svg.png]/wiki/Wikipedia:Protection_policy#semi\\\\\\\\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTutorial for new editors\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIntroduction to Wikipedia\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWikipedia [/wiki/Wikipedia] is made by people like you\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Special:RecentChanges].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis page takes you through a set of tutorials aimed at complete newcomers who\\\\\\\\nwish to contribute. It covers all the basics, and each tutorial takes only a few\\\\\\\\nminutes, so you can become a proficient Wikipedian [/wiki/Wikipedia:Wikipedians]\\\\\\\\nquickly.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nGet started [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_Wikipedia]\\\\\\\\nPolicies and Guidelines [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_policies_and_guidelines/1]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bb/Source_editor_logo.svg/250px-Source_editor_logo.svg.png]/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_editing_with_Wiki_Markup/1\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe wiki markup source editor [/wiki/Help:Wikitext] shows the underlying page\\\\\\\\nsource code. It works like a plain text file, indicating links and other items\\\\\\\\nusing simple code like this: [[Earth]].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEditing [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_editing_with_Wiki_Markup/1]\\\\\\\\nReferencing [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_Wiki_Markup/1]\\\\\\\\nImages [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_images_with_Wiki_Markup/1]\\\\\\\\nTables [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_tables_with_Wiki_Markup/1]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/12/VisualEditor-logo.svg/250px-VisualEditor-logo.svg.png]/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_editing_with_VisualEditor/1\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nVisualEditor [/wiki/Help:VisualEditor] is the easier way of editing that works\\\\\\\\nmore like a word processor and hides the underlying source code. Links and other\\\\\\\\nitems are edited using toolbar and pop-up interfaces.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEditing [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_editing_with_VisualEditor/1]\\\\\\\\nReferencing [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_referencing_with_VisualEditor/1]\\\\\\\\nImages [/wiki/Help:Introduction_to_images_with_VisualEditor/1]\\\\\\\\nTables Tables\\\\\\\\n[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/J/Josh_Schache.html],\\\\\\\\nAustralianFootball.com\\\\\\\\n[https://australianfootball.com/players/player/Josh+Schache/19418]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nJoshua Schache (/ki/ [/wiki/Help:IPA/English] SHAK-ee\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Pronunciation_respelling_key];[1] born 21 August 1997) is an\\\\\\\\nAustralian rules footballer [/wiki/Australian_rules_football] who formerly\\\\\\\\nplayed professionally for the Brisbane Lions [/wiki/Brisbane_Lions], the Western\\\\\\\\nBulldogs [/wiki/Western_Bulldogs] and Melbourne [/wiki/Melbourne_Football_Club]\\\\\\\\nin the Australian Football League [/wiki/Australian_Football_League] (AFL).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEARLY LIFE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Josh_Schache&action=edit&section=1]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache was born in Adelaide, South Australia [/wiki/Adelaide,_South_Australia]\\\\\\\\nto mother Rachel and father Laurence [/wiki/Laurence_Schache].[2] He started\\\\\\\\nplaying Auskick [/wiki/Auskick] when he was in grade five. He attended high\\\\\\\\nschool at Assumption College Kilmore [/wiki/Assumption_College,_Kilmore] and\\\\\\\\nlater Goulburn Valley Grammar School [/wiki/Goulburn_Valley_Grammar_School]. His\\\\\\\\nlate father, Laurence [/wiki/Laurence_Schache], also played with Brisbane in the\\\\\\\\nearly 1990s.[3][4][5]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nJosh spent his early youth as a ruckman/forward for the Seymour Lions, a club\\\\\\\\nbased in the Seymour District Junior Football League. He played with the Murray\\\\\\\\nBushrangers [/wiki/Murray_Bushrangers] in the TAC Cup [/wiki/TAC_Cup] until he\\\\\\\\nwas selected to join the Brisbane Lions with the second pick in the 2015 AFL\\\\\\\\ndraft [/wiki/2015_AFL_draft].[4]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache is left-footed, 199 centimetres (78in) tall and weighs 96 kilograms\\\\\\\\n(212lb).[6]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHe won the Larke Medal [/wiki/Larke_Medal] for his performance in the NAB AFL\\\\\\\\nUnder-18 Championships in 2015, where he also he kicked a record 24 goals.[6]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAFL CAREER\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Josh_Schache&action=edit&section=2]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn the first two years of his career at the Brisbane Lions\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Brisbane_Lions], Schache played 27 games and kicked 25 goals. During 2017\\\\\\\\nthere was speculation that he would request a trade to a Victorian club, but at\\\\\\\\nthe end of the season his manager shut down speculation, insisting that he would\\\\\\\\nnot be requesting a trade. Despite this, Brisbane later announced they would be\\\\\\\\nexploring trade options for Schache in the forthcoming trade period. In the\\\\\\\\nfinal minutes of the trade period, Schache was traded to the Western Bulldogs\\\\\\\\nfor pick 25 and 40 despite being contracted until 2019 at the Brisbane\\\\\\\\nLions.[7]Schache overcame niggling injuries during the first half of 2018. After\\\\\\\\nstrong performances in the VFL he was elevated to the senior side where he\\\\\\\\nfinished the season with 17 goals in 13 games.[8]Schache had a breakout year in\\\\\\\\n2019, kicking 24 goals from 14 games, only being omitted from the side due to\\\\\\\\nconcussion protocols. Schache played in the 2019 Elimination Final against club\\\\\\\\nrivals, Greater Western Sydney. After playing his career best year, Schache only\\\\\\\\nmanaged to play two senior games in 2020, kicking 2 goals.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAfter a one-off appearance earlier in 2021, he returned to the senior side in\\\\\\\\nthe middle of the season, successfully moving to become a key defender.[9]\\\\\\\\nSchache managed to play every game for the rest of the year, as a defender too,\\\\\\\\nincluding the clubs impressive climb to the Grand Final. Schache was moved back\\\\\\\\nto the forward line for the 2021 finals [/wiki/2021_AFL_finals_series], kicking\\\\\\\\n4 goals and shutting down prominent key defenders such as Aliir Aliir\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Aliir_Aliir] of Port Adelaide [/wiki/Port_Adelaide_Football_Club].[10] He\\\\\\\\nplayed in the Western Bulldogs' 2021 Grand Final [/wiki/2021_AFL_Grand_Final]\\\\\\\\nteam.[11]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFollowing the 2022 AFL season [/wiki/2022_AFL_season], Schache was traded to\\\\\\\\nMelbourne [/wiki/Melbourne_Football_Club] on the last day of the trade\\\\\\\\nperiod.[12] Schache managed only four games across two seasons for the Demons.\\\\\\\\nWhen Melbourne failed to make finals for the first time since 2020, Schache was\\\\\\\\ndelisted at the conclusion of the 2024 AFL season [/wiki/2024_AFL_season].[13]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn 2025, Schache will play for the Doncaster East Football Club\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Doncaster_East_Football_Club] in the Eastern Football Netball League\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Eastern_Football_Netball_League] (EFNL).[14]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSTATISTICS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Josh_Schache&action=edit&section=3]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUpdated to the end of (78)[1]\\\\\\\\n1 Playing statistics correct to the end of 1992.\\\\\\\\nCareer highlights\\\\\\\\n * 1991  Leading goalkicker, Brisbane (47 goals)\\\\\\\\n * 1993 Premiership Player Woodville-West Torrens\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Woodville-West_Torrens_Football_Club] (SANFL\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/South_Australian_National_Football_League])\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSources: AFL Tables\\\\\\\\n[http://afltables.com/afl/stats/players/L/Laurence_Schache.html],\\\\\\\\nAustralianFootball.com\\\\\\\\n[https://australianfootball.com/players/player/Laurence+Schache/12849]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nLaurence Schache (/ki/ [/wiki/Help:IPA/English] SHAK-ee\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Help:Pronunciation_respelling_key];[2] 17 October 1967  5 October 2002)\\\\\\\\nwas an Australian rules footballer [/wiki/Australian_rules_football], playing in\\\\\\\\nthe Australian Football League [/wiki/Australian_Football_League] (AFL) with the\\\\\\\\nBrisbane Bears [/wiki/Brisbane_Bears] and the South Australian National Football\\\\\\\\nLeague [/wiki/South_Australian_National_Football_League] (SANFL) with Sturt\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Sturt_Football_Club], West Torrens [/wiki/West_Torrens_Football_Club] and\\\\\\\\nWoodville-West Torrens [/wiki/Woodville-West_Torrens_Eagles].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEARLY LIFE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Laurence_Schache&action=edit&section=1]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBorn in Hopetoun, Victoria [/wiki/Hopetoun,_Victoria], Schache was zoned\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Zoning_(Australian_rules_football)] to the Essendon Football Club\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Essendon_Football_Club] in the Victorian Football League\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Australian_Football_League]. He played in the minor grades at Essendon as\\\\\\\\na forward with some success, which included a haul of 25 goals in an under-19s\\\\\\\\nmatch against Sydney [/wiki/Sydney_Swans] in round 22, 1985,[3] but he never\\\\\\\\nmanaged to play a senior game for Essendon.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache moved to Adelaide [/wiki/Adelaide] in 1988 to play for Sturt,[4] before\\\\\\\\nmoving to West Torrens in 1989.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAFL CAREER\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Laurence_Schache&action=edit&section=2]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache was drafted by Brisbane as the number one choice at the 1990 Mid Year\\\\\\\\nAFL National Draft [/wiki/1989_VFL_Draft#1990_Midyear_Draft] and made his AFL\\\\\\\\ndebut for the Bears against Geelong [/wiki/Geelong_Football_Club] in round 4,\\\\\\\\n1991.[5]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache played 17 games for Brisbane in 1991, winning the club's leading\\\\\\\\ngoalkicker award in his first season with 47 goals, including a best return of\\\\\\\\nsix goals against Adelaide [/wiki/Adelaide_Football_Club] in round 14. Schache\\\\\\\\nhad a less successful year in 1992, playing 12 games for 17 goals, and\\\\\\\\nsubsequently was delisted by Brisbane at the end of the season after 29 games\\\\\\\\nand 64 goals.[6]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache returned to South Australia [/wiki/South_Australia] in 1993 to play for\\\\\\\\nthe Woodville-West Torrens Eagles (West Torrens having merged with fellow SANFL\\\\\\\\nclub Woodville [/wiki/Woodville_Football_Club] at the end of 1990). Schache\\\\\\\\nplayed in the Eagles's first premiership but injured his knee the following\\\\\\\\nyear, forcing his retirement.[4]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDEATH\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Laurence_Schache&action=edit&section=3]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSchache briefly coached Latrobe Football Club [/wiki/Latrobe_Football_Club] in\\\\\\\\nTasmania before returning to Adelaide, where he was diagnosed with amyloidosis\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Amyloidosis] in July 2002.[6] Initially told he had five years to live,\\\\\\\\nSchache collapsed and died at his home, three months later.[6] He was 34 and\\\\\\\\nleft a widow and two children.[4]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFAMILY\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Laurence_Schache&action=edit&section=4]]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHis son Josh [/wiki/Josh_Schache] is also an Australian rules footballer. Josh\\\\\\\\nwas the No. 2 selection in the 2015 AFL draft [/wiki/2015_AFL_draft],[7] and\\\\\\\\nplayed for Melbourne [/wiki/Melbourne_Football_Club], Brisbane Lions\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Brisbane_Lions] and Western Bulldogs [/wiki/Western_Bulldogs] between\\\\\\\\n2016 and 2024.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nREFERENCES\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[edit [/w/index.php?title=Laurence_Schache&action=edit&section=5]]\\\\\\\\n 1. ^ Capel, Andrew (10 July 2015). \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Possible No. 1 draft pick Josh Schache\\\\\\\\n    following in the footsteps of his late dad Laurence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n    [http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/sport/afl/possible-no-1-draft-pick-josh-schache-following-in-the-footsteps-of-his-late-dad-laurence/story-fnii0294-1227436898296].\\\\\\\\n    News Corporation. articles in English\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/English_language]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFROM TODAY'S FEATURED ARTICLE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe Championship Course, along which the Boat Race is contested\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/University_Boat_Race_Thames_map.svg/250px-University_Boat_Race_Thames_map.svg.png]/wiki/File:University_Boat_Race_Thames_map.svg\\\\\\\\nThe Championship Course, along which the Boat Race is contested\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe Boat Race 2020 [/wiki/The_Boat_Race_2020] was a side-by-side rowing\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Rowing_(sport)#Side_by_side] race scheduled to take place on 29March\\\\\\\\n2020. Held annually, the Boat Race [/wiki/The_Boat_Race] is contested between\\\\\\\\ncrews from the University of Oxford [/wiki/University_of_Oxford] and the\\\\\\\\nUniversity of Cambridge [/wiki/University_of_Cambridge] along a 4.2-mile\\\\\\\\n(6.8km) tidal stretch of the River Thames [/wiki/River_Thames] (course\\\\\\\\npictured) in south-west London. This would have been the 75th women's race\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Women%27s_Boat_Race] and the 166th men's race. Cambridge led the\\\\\\\\nlongstanding rivalry 8480 and 4430 in the men's and women's races,\\\\\\\\nrespectively. The races were cancelled on 16March 2020 as a consequence of the\\\\\\\\nCOVID-19 pandemic in the United Kingdom\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/COVID-19_pandemic_in_the_United_Kingdom]. Other than as a result of war,\\\\\\\\nit was the first time that the men's race had been cancelled since the first\\\\\\\\nedition in 1845 [/wiki/The_Boat_Race_1845]. It was also the first cancellation\\\\\\\\nof the women's race since its 1964 revival. The 2020 event would have been the\\\\\\\\nfirst time that both senior races would be umpired by women. The members of each\\\\\\\\ncrew were announced on the date that the race would have been contested.\\\\\\\\n(Fullarticle... [/wiki/The_Boat_Race_2020])\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRecently featured:\\\\\\\\n * Dolly de Leon [/wiki/Dolly_de_Leon]\\\\\\\\n * Banded sugar ant [/wiki/Banded_sugar_ant]\\\\\\\\n * Mirella Freni [/wiki/Mirella_Freni] (pictured) and Luciano Pavarotti\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Luciano_Pavarotti], who co-starred as the lovers Mim and Rodolfo in\\\\\\\\n   La bohme [/wiki/La_boh%C3%A8me] at La Scala [/wiki/La_Scala] in 1968, shared\\\\\\\\n   the same wet nurse [/wiki/Wet_nurse]?\\\\\\\\n * ... that Bill Chisholm [/wiki/Bill_Chisholm_(businessman)]'s announced $6.1\\\\\\\\n   billion purchase of the Boston Celtics [/wiki/Boston_Celtics] is the largest\\\\\\\\n   amount ever paid for a North American sports team?\\\\\\\\n * ... that a former management consultant who coined the framework of \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"The\\\\\\\\n   Three Worlds of Evangelicalism [/wiki/The_Three_Worlds_of_Evangelicalism]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\n   was described by The New York Times [/wiki/The_New_York_Times] as \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"a kind of\\\\\\\\n   Malcolm Gladwell [/wiki/Malcolm_Gladwell] of conservative Christianity\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Conservative_Christianity]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\\n * ... that the 2001 Zug massacre [/wiki/Zug_massacre] resulted in changes to\\\\\\\\n   security measures for public buildings, but not to Swiss gun laws\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Firearms_regulation_in_Switzerland]?\\\\\\\\n * ... that Juan Soto, before his blockbuster trade [/wiki/Juan_Soto_trade],\\\\\\\\n   rejected a 15-year, $440million contract extension, which would have been\\\\\\\\n   the largest deal in Major League Baseball history at the time?\\\\\\\\n * ... that about 25 percent of people experience heartburn [/wiki/Heartburn] at\\\\\\\\n   least once a month?\\\\\\\\n * ... that Miroslav Kvoka [/wiki/Miroslav_Kvo%C4%8Dka] was convicted of war\\\\\\\\n   crimes [/wiki/War_crime] and crimes against humanity\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Crimes_against_humanity] against non-Serb detainees in the Omarska\\\\\\\\n   concentration camp [/wiki/Omarska_camp] during the Bosnian War\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Bosnian_War]?\\\\\\\\n * ... that the Edmonds' Clock Tower [/wiki/Edmonds%27_Clock_Tower] was split in\\\\\\\\n   two after the June2011 Christchurch earthquakes\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/June_2011_Christchurch_earthquake]?\\\\\\\\n * ... that the Overwatch [/wiki/Overwatch] character Juno\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Juno_(Overwatch)] has been praised for her ability to reward players\\\\\\\\n   for having sound game sense?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Archive [/wiki/Wikipedia:Recent_additions]\\\\\\\\n * Start a new article [/wiki/Help:Your_first_article]\\\\\\\\n * Nominate an Cliburn\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/17/Van_Cliburn_1966b.jpg/250px-Van_Cliburn_1966b.jpg]/wiki/File:Van_Cliburn_1966b.jpg\\\\\\\\nVan Cliburn\\\\\\\\n * 1777 [/wiki/1777]  American Revolutionary War\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/American_Revolutionary_War]: British and Hessian\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Hessian_(soldier)] forces conducted a surprise attack\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Battle_of_Bound_Brook] against a Continental Army\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Continental_Army] outpost at Bound Brook, New Jersey\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Bound_Brook,_New_Jersey].\\\\\\\\n * 1829 [/wiki/1829]  The Roman Catholic Relief Act\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Relief_Act_1829] received royal assent\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Royal_assent], removing the most substantial restrictions on Catholics\\\\\\\\n   in the United Kingdom [/wiki/Catholic_Church_in_the_United_Kingdom].\\\\\\\\n * 1958 [/wiki/1958]  In the midst of the Cold War [/wiki/Cold_War], American\\\\\\\\n   pianist Van Cliburn [/wiki/Van_Cliburn] (pictured) won the inaugural\\\\\\\\n   International Tchaikovsky Competition\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/International_Tchaikovsky_Competition] in Moscow.\\\\\\\\n * 2009 [/wiki/2009]  Twenty-three people died in a fire at a homeless hostel\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Kamie%C5%84_Pomorski_homeless_hostel_fire] in Kamie Pomorski\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Kamie%C5%84_Pomorski]; it was Poland's deadliest fire since 1980.\\\\\\\\n * 2017 [/wiki/2017]  War in Afghanistan\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/War_in_Afghanistan_(2001%E2%80%932021)]: In an airstrike\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/2017_Nangarhar_airstrike] in Nangarhar Province\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Nangarhar_Province], the U.S. military dropped the most powerful\\\\\\\\n   conventional bomb used in combat [/wiki/GBU-43/B_MOAB].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Henry De la Beche [/wiki/Henry_De_la_Beche] (d.1855)\\\\\\\\n * Annie Jump Cannon [/wiki/Annie_Jump_Cannon] (d.1941)\\\\\\\\n * Gnter Grass [/wiki/G%C3%BCnter_Grass] (d.2015)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nMore anniversaries:\\\\\\\\n * April 12 [/wiki/April_12]\\\\\\\\n * April 13 [/wiki/April_13]\\\\\\\\n * April 14 [/wiki/April_14]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Archive [/wiki/Wikipedia:Selected_anniversaries/April]\\\\\\\\n * By email\\\\\\\\n   [https://lists.wikimedia.org/postorius/lists/daily-article-l.lists.wikimedia.org/]\\\\\\\\n * List of days of the year [/wiki/List_of_days_of_the_year]\\\\\\\\n * About [/wiki/Wikipedia:Selected_anniversaries]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nTODAY'S FEATURED PICTURE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThomas Jefferson\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/JEFFERSON%2C_Thomas-President_%28BEP_engraved_portrait%29.jpg/500px-JEFFERSON%2C_Thomas-President_%28BEP_engraved_portrait%29.jpg]/wiki/File:JEFFERSON,_Thomas-President_(BEP_engraved_portrait).jpg\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThomas Jefferson [/wiki/Thomas_Jefferson] (April13, 1743 July4, 1826) was an\\\\\\\\nAmerican statesman, planter, diplomat, lawyer, architect, philosopher, and\\\\\\\\nFounding Father [/wiki/Founding_Fathers_of_the_United_States] who served as the\\\\\\\\nthird president of the United States [/wiki/President_of_the_United_States] from\\\\\\\\n1801 to 1809. He was the primary author of the Declaration of Independence\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/United_States_Declaration_of_Independence]. Following the American\\\\\\\\nRevolutionary War [/wiki/American_Revolutionary_War] and before becoming\\\\\\\\npresident in 1801, Jefferson was the first United States secretary of state\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/United_States_Secretary_of_State] under George Washington\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/George_Washington], and then the second vice president\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Vice_President_of_the_United_States] under John Adams [/wiki/John_Adams].\\\\\\\\nJefferson was a leading proponent of democracy, republicanism\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Republicanism], and natural rights [/wiki/Natural_law], and he produced\\\\\\\\nformative documents and decisions at the state, national, and international\\\\\\\\nlevels. This line-engraved [/wiki/Line_engraving] portrait of Jefferson was\\\\\\\\nproduced by the United States Department of the Treasury\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/United_States_Department_of_the_Treasury]'s Bureau of Engraving and\\\\\\\\nPrinting [/wiki/Bureau_of_Engraving_and_Printing] (BEP) as part of a BEP\\\\\\\\npresentation album [/wiki/US_Treasury_specimen_book] of the first 26 presidents.\\\\\\\\nThe same portrait appears on the obverse of the two-dollar bill\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/United_States_two-dollar_bill].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEngraving credit: Bureau of Engraving and Printing\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Bureau_of_Engraving_and_Printing]; restored by Andrew Shiva\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/User:Godot13]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRecently featured:\\\\\\\\n * Bali myna (SOHR)\\\\\\\\n         [https://www.syriahr.com/%d8%b4%d9%87%d8%b1-%d9%83%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%84-%d8%b9%d9%84%d9%89-%d9%85%d8%b0%d8%a8%d8%ad%d8%a9-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b3%d8%a7%d8%ad%d9%84-%d8%a7%d9%84%d8%b3%d9%88%d8%b1%d9%8a-%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%86%d8%aa%d8%b8/755870/]\\\\\\\\n * Gaza war [/wiki/Gaza_war]\\\\\\\\n   * Israeli occupation of the Gaza Strip\\\\\\\\n     [/wiki/Israeli_occupation_of_the_Gaza_Strip]\\\\\\\\n     * Israel [/wiki/Israel] reportedly controls over half of the territory of\\\\\\\\n       the Gaza Strip [/wiki/Gaza_Strip] after razing [/wiki/Razing] multiple\\\\\\\\n       Palestinian properties to expand its buffer zone [/wiki/Buffer_zone].\\\\\\\\n       (AP)\\\\\\\\n       [https://apnews.com/article/gaza-buffer-zone-ceasefire-b7dada19483a3f8ef2fdecbc745ee6b5]\\\\\\\\n       (CNN)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.cnn.com/2025/04/07/middleeast/israel-gaza-buffer-zone-troops-intl/index.html]\\\\\\\\n   * An Israeli [/wiki/Israel_Defense_Forces] airstrike [/wiki/Airstrike] near a\\\\\\\\n     charity kitchen in Gaza [/wiki/Gaza_Strip] where displaced\\\\\\\\n     [/wiki/Internal_displacement] Palestinians [/wiki/Palestinians] gather for\\\\\\\\n     food, kills more than 30 people. (AP)\\\\\\\\n     [https://apnews.com/article/israel-palestinians-hamas-war-news-ceasefire-hostages-04-07-2025-1ef0696b9c12bf18b5123ccd5b384a02]\\\\\\\\n * Herderfarmer conflicts in Nigeria\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Herder%E2%80%93farmer_conflicts_in_Nigeria]\\\\\\\\n   * The National Emergency Management Agency\\\\\\\\n     [/wiki/National_Emergency_Management_Agency_(Nigeria)] reports that at\\\\\\\\n     least 52 people have been killed and over 2,000 others have been displaced\\\\\\\\n     from their homes in recent days in tit for tat [/wiki/Tit_for_tat] attacks\\\\\\\\n     by rival herders over control of arable land [/wiki/Arable_land] in Plateau\\\\\\\\n     State [/wiki/Plateau_State], Nigeria [/wiki/Nigeria]. (Reuters)\\\\\\\\n     [https://www.reuters.com/world/africa/gunmen-kill-least-52-people-nigerias-plateau-state-2025-04-07/]\\\\\\\\n * Insurgency in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa [/wiki/Insurgency_in_Khyber_Pakhtunkhwa]\\\\\\\\n   * A Pakistan Army [/wiki/Pakistan_Army] raid on a Pakistani Taliban\\\\\\\\n     [/wiki/Pakistani_Taliban] militant hideout in Dera Ismail Khan\\\\\\\\n     [/wiki/Dera_Ismail_Khan], Khyber Pakhtunkhwa [/wiki/Khyber_Pakhtunkhwa],\\\\\\\\n     kills nine militants, including a high-profile Taliban leader who\\\\\\\\n     coordinated recent attacks on Pakistani military facilities in the region.\\\\\\\\n     (AP)\\\\\\\\n     [https://apnews.com/article/pakistan-security-raid-militants-killed-northwest-9c73a1b91b3697b4928870c7e4645671]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nBusiness and economy\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Tariffs in the second Trump administration\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Tariffs_in_the_second_Trump_administration], Executive orders in the\\\\\\\\n   second presidency of Donald Trump\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/List_of_executive_orders_in_the_second_presidency_of_Donald_Trump]\\\\\\\\n   * Executive Order 14257 [/wiki/Donald_Trump%27s_Liberation_Day_speech]\\\\\\\\n     * The Nikkei 225 [/wiki/Nikkei_225], SSE Composite Index\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/SSE_Composite_Index], and Hang Seng Index [/wiki/Hang_Seng_Index]\\\\\\\\n       experience substantial losses following Fridays losses on the New York\\\\\\\\n       Stock Exchange [/wiki/New_York_Stock_Exchange] as a result of U.S.\\\\\\\\n       president [/wiki/President_of_the_United_States] Donald Trump\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Donald_Trump]'s tariffs [/wiki/Tariff]. European markets\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Economy_of_Europe] also decline, particularly in banking\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Bank] and defense sectors [/wiki/Arms_industry]. The ASX 200\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/ASX_200] in Australia [/wiki/Australia] and the Kospi\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Kospi] in South Korea [/wiki/South_Korea] also closes lower. (BBC\\\\\\\\n       News) [https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c934qzd094wo]\\\\\\\\n     * European Commission [/wiki/European_Commission] president\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/President_of_the_European_Commission] Ursula von der Leyen\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Ursula_von_der_Leyen] offers to negotiate with Trump to avoid a\\\\\\\\n       trade war [/wiki/Trade_war] and further economic panic, including a\\\\\\\\n       zero-for-zero tariff deal on all industrial goods\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Industrial_engineering]. (Politico)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.politico.eu/article/eu-offers-trump-removal-of-all-tariffs/]\\\\\\\\n       (Euronews)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2025/04/07/von-der-leyen-offers-trump-zero-for-zero-tariffs-deal-on-all-industrial-goods]\\\\\\\\n     * Taiwanese president [/wiki/President_of_Taiwan] Lai Ching-te\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Lai_Ching-te] states that he does not intend to implement\\\\\\\\n       retaliatory tariffs against the United States. He instead expressed\\\\\\\\n       Taiwan [/wiki/Taiwan]'s intent to import more American exports\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/Foreign_trade_of_the_United_States] and increase its investments\\\\\\\\n       in the U.S. economy [/wiki/Economy_of_the_United_States], beginning with\\\\\\\\n       a proposal for a TaiwanU.S. bilateral zero-tariff deal. (NBC News)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/trump-administration/live-blog/trump-netanyahu-tariffs-live-updates-rcna199871/rcrd76472?canonicalCard=true]\\\\\\\\n     * President Trump announces plans to impose\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/China%E2%80%93United_States_trade_war] a 50% tariff on China\\\\\\\\n       [/wiki/China], escalating to a total of 104% if China does not revoke its\\\\\\\\n       34% reciprocal tariff on all American goods within a day. China rejects\\\\\\\\n       the ultimatum [/wiki/Ultimatum], maintains its reciprocal tariffs, and\\\\\\\\n       states its intention to match any further escalation. (CNBC)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.cnbc.com/2025/04/07/trump-tariffs-live-updates-stock-market-crypto.html]\\\\\\\\n       (NBC News)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/trump-administration/live-blog/trump-netanyahu-tariffs-live-updates-rcna199871#rcrd76516]\\\\\\\\n       (AFP via Barron's)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.barrons.com/news/china-will-not-bow-to-fresh-trump-tariff-threat-embassy-says-f8a373f6]\\\\\\\\n       (Reuters)\\\\\\\\n       [https://www.reuters.com/world/china-criticises-trump-tariff-blackmail-market-turmoil-settles-2025-04-08/]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nInternational relations\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * AlgeriaMali relations [/wiki/Algeria%E2%80%93Mali_relations]\\\\\\\\n   * Algeria [/wiki/Algeria] bans flights to and from Mali [/wiki/Mali] in\\\\\\\\n     response to \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"recurrent violations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" of Algerian airspace [/wiki/Airspace] by\\\\\\\\n     Malian military [/wiki/Malian_Armed_Forces] drones. hide\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis page contains a list of special pages [/wiki/Help:Special_page]. Most of\\\\\\\\nthe content of these pages is automatically generated and cannot be edited. To\\\\\\\\nsuggest a change to the parts that can be edited, find the appropriate text on\\\\\\\\nSpecial:AllMessages [/wiki/Special:AllMessages] and then request your change on\\\\\\\\nthe talk page of the message (using {{editprotected\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Edit_fully-protected]}} to draw the attention of\\\\\\\\nadministrators).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou can also see what message names are used on a page by adding ?uselang=qqx to\\\\\\\\nthe end of its URL, e.g.\\\\\\\\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:SpecialPages?uselang=qqx\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:SpecialPages?uselang=qqx] will show\\\\\\\\n(specialpages-summary) in place of this message, which allows you to find\\\\\\\\nMediaWiki:Specialpages-summary [/wiki/MediaWiki:Specialpages-summary].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFor an index of special pages, see
