sidebar hide\\\\\\\\nFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWikimedia file upload wizard\\\\\\\\nShortcut [/wiki/Wikipedia:Shortcut]\\\\\\\\n * WP:FUW [https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:FUW&redirect=no]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThank you for offering to contribute an image or other media file for use on\\\\\\\\nWikipedia. This wizard will guide you through a questionnaire prompting you for\\\\\\\\nthe appropriate copyright and sourcing information for each file. Please ensure\\\\\\\\nyou understand copyright [/wiki/Wikipedia:Copyrights] and the image use policy\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Image_use_policy] before proceeding.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUpload your own or a freely licensed file\\\\\\\\n[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:UploadWizard]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUploads to Wikimedia Commons [/wiki/Wikipedia:Wikimedia_Commons]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUpload a non-free file\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:File_upload_wizard&withJS=MediaWiki:FileUploadWizard.js&withCSS=MediaWiki:FileUploadWizard.css]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUploads locally to the English Wikipedia; must comply with the non-free content\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Non-free_content] criteria\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou do not have JavaScript enabled\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSorry, in order to use this uploading script, JavaScript must be enabled. You\\\\\\\\ncan still use the plain Special:Upload [/wiki/Special:Upload] page to upload\\\\\\\\nfiles to the English Wikipedia without JavaScript.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou are not currently logged in.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSorry, in order to use this uploading script and to upload files, you need to be\\\\\\\\nlogged in with your named account. Please log in\\\\\\\\n[https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:UserLogin&returnto=Wikipedia%3AFile+Upload+Wizard&returntoquery=withJS%3DMediaWiki%253AFileUploadWizard.js]\\\\\\\\nand then try again.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYour account has not become confirmed yet.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSorry, in order to upload files on the English Wikipedia, you need to have a\\\\\\\\nconfirmed account [/wiki/Wikipedia:AUTOCONFIRM]. Normally, your account will\\\\\\\\nbecome confirmed automatically once you have made 10 edits and four days have\\\\\\\\npassed since you created it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYou may already be able to upload files on the Wikimedia Commons\\\\\\\\n[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/], but you can't do it on the English\\\\\\\\nWikipedia just yet. If the file you want to upload has a free license, please go\\\\\\\\nto Commons and upload it there.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nImportant note: if you don't want to wait until you are autoconfirmed, you may\\\\\\\\nask somebody else to upload a file for you at Wikipedia:Files for upload\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Files_for_upload].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn very rare cases an administrator may make your account confirmed manually\\\\\\\\nthrough a request at Wikipedia:Requests for permissions/Confirmed\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Requests_for_permissions/Confirmed].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSTEP 1: CHOOSE YOUR FILE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFile:\\\\\\\\nChoose a file from your computer. Maximum file size: 100 MB.\\\\\\\\nPermitted file types: png, gif, jpg, jpeg, xcf, pdf, mid, mp3, mpeg, mpg, ogg,\\\\\\\\nogv, opus, svg, djvu, tiff, tif, oga, flac, wav, wave, webm, webp.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSTEP 2: DESCRIBE YOUR FILE\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease provide a clear, descriptive name by which your file will be known on\\\\\\\\nWikipedia.\\\\\\\\nThis name must be unique across the whole of Wikipedia, so please make it\\\\\\\\ninformative and easy to recognize.\\\\\\\\nIt's no problem to use a fairly long name. It may also include spaces, commas\\\\\\\\nand most other punctuation marks.\\\\\\\\nPlease also note that file names are case sensitive (with the exception of the\\\\\\\\nfirst letter).\\\\\\\\nGood: \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"City of London, skyline from London City Hall, Oct 2008.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\". Bad:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Skyline.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"DSC0001234.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSorry, a few special characters and character combinations cannot be used in the\\\\\\\\nfilename for technical reasons. This goes especially for #<>[]|:{}/\\\\\\\\nand ~~~. Your filename has been modified to avoid these. Please check if it is\\\\\\\\nokay now.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe filename you chose seems to be very short, or overly generic. Please don't\\\\\\\\nuse:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * Titles that consist only of very generic descriptive words (e.g.\\\\\\\\n   \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Sunset.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Townhall.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n * Titles that consist only of a person's first or last name, when that name is\\\\\\\\n   likely to be shared by many others (e.g. \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"John.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Miller.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n * Titles that consist of mere numbers, of the kind often produced by digital\\\\\\\\n   cameras (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"DSC_001234\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"IMGP0345\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), or random strings like those sometimes\\\\\\\\n   found on the web (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"30996951316264l.jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\")\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a9/Example.jpg/250px-Example.jpg]/wiki/File:Example.jpgExisting\\\\\\\\nfile [/wiki/File:Example.jpg].\\\\\\\\nLast uploaded by Example user.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA file of this name already exists on Commons!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you upload your file with this name, you will be masking the existing file\\\\\\\\nand make it inaccessible. Your new file will be displayed everywhere the\\\\\\\\nexisting file was previously used.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis should not be done, except in very rare exceptional cases.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease don't upload your file under this name, unless you seriously know what\\\\\\\\nyou are doing. Choose a different name for your new file instead.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you want to replace the existing file with an uncontroversial, improved\\\\\\\\nversion of the same work, please go to Commons and upload it there, not here on\\\\\\\\nthe English Wikipedia's local wiki.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nA file of this name already exists.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you upload your file with this name, you will be overwriting the existing\\\\\\\\nfile. Your new file will be displayed everywhere the existing file was\\\\\\\\npreviously used. Please don't do this, unless you have a good reason to:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNo, I don't want to overwrite the existing file. I will choose a different name\\\\\\\\nfor my new file instead.Yes, I want to overwrite the existing file. My file is\\\\\\\\nmerely a new, improved and uncontentious version of the same work. The old\\\\\\\\ndescription page, including the source and copyright information, will still be\\\\\\\\ncorrect for the new version and can remain the same.Yes, I want to overwrite the\\\\\\\\nexisting file, and I will use this wizard to add a new description and new\\\\\\\\nsource information for it. The previous version was my own, or else I have made\\\\\\\\nsure the previous uploader(s) don't object to this replacement.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease provide a brief description of the contents of this file.\\\\\\\\nThis will be stored and displayed as part of the file description page. It is\\\\\\\\nimportant that other editors are able to understand what this file is about.\\\\\\\\nWhat does this file show? What is it a photo/diagram/recording of?\\\\\\\\nIt will be helpful if you also add a wikilink\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Cheatsheet#Internal_link] to the article where you want to use\\\\\\\\nit.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSTEP 3: PROVIDE SOURCE AND COPYRIGHT INFORMATION\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt is very important that you read through the following options and questions,\\\\\\\\nand provide all required information truthfully and carefully.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is a free work.\\\\\\\\nI can demonstrate that it is legally okay for anybody to use, in Wikipedia and\\\\\\\\nelsewhere, for any purpose.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThank you for offering to upload a free work.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWikipedia loves free files. However, we would love it even more if you uploaded\\\\\\\\nthem on our sister project, Wikimedia Commons\\\\\\\\n[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/].Files uploaded on Commons can be used\\\\\\\\nimmediately here on Wikipedia as well as on all its sister projects. Uploading\\\\\\\\nfiles on Commons works just the same as here. Your Wikipedia account will\\\\\\\\nautomatically work on Commons too.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Gtk-dialog-info.svg/40px-Gtk-dialog-info.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nPlease consider uploading your file on Commons\\\\\\\\n[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:UploadWizard].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHowever, if you prefer to do it here instead, you may go ahead with this form.\\\\\\\\nYou can also first use this form to collect the information about your file and\\\\\\\\nthen send it to Commons from here.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nCopyright status:This file is entirely my own work.\\\\\\\\nI am the copyright holder. I made this myself, from scratch, without copying or\\\\\\\\nincorporating anybody else's creative work, and I am willing to release it under\\\\\\\\na free license.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease note that by \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"entirely self-made\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" we really mean just that.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nDo not use this section for any of the following:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * a scan or photograph you made of a painting, drawing, printed page or other\\\\\\\\n   item originally created by somebody else. The copyright belongs to the\\\\\\\\n   original creator, not to you.\\\\\\\\n * a screenshot or other kind of capture of a video, computer screen, TV\\\\\\\\n   programme or other kind of visual media.\\\\\\\\n * a picture you created by modifying or copying some other picture or by\\\\\\\\n   combining several preexisting pictures made by somebody else.\\\\\\\\n * a picture given to you by somebody else.\\\\\\\\n * a picture you found somewhere on the Internet.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEditors who falsely declare such items as their \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"own work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" will be blocked from\\\\\\\\nediting.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease describe how and when you created this item.How?(e.g.: Where and on what\\\\\\\\nkind of occasion did you take this photo? How did you make this diagram?\\\\\\\\netc.)Date(please use YYYY-MM-DD format if possible).Publication:\\\\\\\\nPlease indicate here if you have previously published this item elsewhere, e.g.\\\\\\\\non your own website, your Flickr or Facebook account, etc., providing a link.It\\\\\\\\nis important that you place this work under a free license, which will allow\\\\\\\\neverybody else to use it for any purpose, including both commercial and\\\\\\\\nnon-commercial purposes, and to modify it. This license will be irrevocable.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis file was given to me by its owner.\\\\\\\\nThe copyright owner of this file has given it to me for uploading on Wikipedia.\\\\\\\\nI can provide evidence that they have agreed to release it under a free license,\\\\\\\\nfor free use by anybody and for any purpose.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease describe who owns this work and how you got it from\\\\\\\\nthem.Owner/author:Date of\\\\\\\\ncreation:Source:\\\\\\\\nWhere did you get the file from? (e.g. available online; was sent to me\\\\\\\\npersonally )Permission:\\\\\\\\nHow did you receive the permission? (e.g.: by e-mail, personally, I work for the\\\\\\\\nowner )The copyright owner has chosen the following license:License:\\\\\\\\nOther: Evidence:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe license statement can be found online at:\\\\\\\\nThe license agreement has been forwarded to Wikimedia's volunteer response team\\\\\\\\nat \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"permissions-en@wikimedia.org\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\nOTRS ticket received: The license hasn't yet been forwarded, but I will do so\\\\\\\\nshortly or ask the owner to send it.I haven't got the evidence right now, but I\\\\\\\\nwill provide some if requested to do so.\\\\\\\\nNote: files without verifiable permissions may be deleted. You may be better off\\\\\\\\nobtaining proof of permission first.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis file is from a free published source.\\\\\\\\nI took it from a website or other published source, where its author has\\\\\\\\nexplicitly placed it under a free license, allowing free re-use by anybody.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUse this only if there is an explicit licensing statement in the source.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe website must explicitly say that the image is released under a license that\\\\\\\\nallows free re-use for any purpose, e.g. the Creative Commons Attribution\\\\\\\\nlicense. You must be able to point exactly to where it says this.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf the source website doesn't say so explicitly, please do not upload the file.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAuthor/owner:Date of\\\\\\\\ncreation:Source:\\\\\\\\nFor web sources: please provide a link to the html web page where the file can\\\\\\\\nbe found (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .html\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), not a direct link to the image file itself\\\\\\\\n(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").\\\\\\\\nFor print sources: provide full bibliographic information (author, title,\\\\\\\\npublisher, year, page, etc.)The copyright owner has chosen the following license\\\\\\\\nfor this file:License:\\\\\\\\nOther: Evidence:\\\\\\\\nProvide a link to where the author explicitly says that the file is released\\\\\\\\nunder a free license.\\\\\\\\n(if not visible on the source page itself).\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis work is so old its copyright has expired\\\\\\\\nThis is an old photograph, or a photographic reproduction of an old painting,\\\\\\\\ndrawing, etc. I can provide enough information about its author and provenance\\\\\\\\nto prove that it is old enough for its copyright to have expired. It is now\\\\\\\\nlegally in the Public Domain [/wiki/Public_Domain].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOriginal\\\\\\\\nauthor:\\\\\\\\nPlease name the original author of this work.Lifetime:\\\\\\\\nSpecify date of death, if applicable to public domain status.\\\\\\\\nIn many cases, we need to be certain the author died before a certain year, in\\\\\\\\nmany cases before 1930.Original\\\\\\\\npublication:\\\\\\\\nProvide as much information as possible about the original time and place of\\\\\\\\npublication of this work. For print publications: provide full bibliographic\\\\\\\\ninformation.Date of\\\\\\\\npublication:\\\\\\\\nProvide date of first publication, and date of creation if different.Immediate\\\\\\\\nsource:\\\\\\\\nState exactly where you found this file.\\\\\\\\nFor web sources: please provide a link to the html web page where the file can\\\\\\\\nbe found (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .html\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), not a direct link to the image file itself\\\\\\\\n(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").\\\\\\\\nFor print sources: provide full bibliographic information (author, title,\\\\\\\\npublisher, year, page, etc.)Public Domain\\\\\\\\nstatus:This work is free of all copyrights because:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt was created and first published before 1930 and is therefore in the Public\\\\\\\\nDomain in the US.It was first published outside the US, and it was in the Public\\\\\\\\nDomain in its country of origin by the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"URAA date\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Uruguay_Round_Agreements_Act]\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\".\\\\\\\\nFor most countries, this means the author died 70 years before 1 January 1996,\\\\\\\\ni.e. before 1926. Please look up the copyright rules for the specific country at\\\\\\\\n[1] [http://copyright.cornell.edu/resources/publicdomain.cfm].It was first\\\\\\\\npublished in the US before 1989, and its copyright expired because it was\\\\\\\\npublished without a copyright notice and/or without the necessary copyright\\\\\\\\nregistration.\\\\\\\\nPlease look up the exact rules at [2]\\\\\\\\n[http://copyright.cornell.edu/resources/publicdomain.cfm].Its copyright expired\\\\\\\\nfor some other reason. [Please explain below].\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nExplanation:\\\\\\\\nPlease provide any evidence necessary to verify the public domain status.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis file is in the Public Domain for some other reason.\\\\\\\\nI can demonstrate that this work is legally in the Public Domain, i.e. nobody\\\\\\\\nowns any copyrights on it. This may be for a variety of reasons, for instance\\\\\\\\nbecause it was created by the US Federal Government, or because it is too simple\\\\\\\\nto attract any copyright.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPublic Domain means that nobody owns any copyrights on this work. It does not\\\\\\\\nmean simply that it is freely viewable somewhere on the web or that it has been\\\\\\\\nwidely used by others.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is not for images you simply found somewhere on the web. Most images on the\\\\\\\\nweb are under copyright and belong to somebody, even if you believe the owner\\\\\\\\nwon't care about that copyright. If it is in the public domain, you must be able\\\\\\\\nto point to an actual law that makes it so. If you can't point to such a law but\\\\\\\\nmerely found this image somewhere, then please do not upload it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAuthor:\\\\\\\\nPlease name the original author of this work.Source:\\\\\\\\nState exactly where you found this file.\\\\\\\\nFor web sources: please provide a link to the html web page where the file can\\\\\\\\nbe found (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .html\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), not a direct link to the image file itself\\\\\\\\n(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").\\\\\\\\nFor print sources: provide full bibliographic information (author, title,\\\\\\\\npublisher, year, page, etc.)Date of\\\\\\\\ncreation:Public Domain\\\\\\\\nstatus:This work is free of all copyrights because:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIt was created by an agency of the US Federal Government.\\\\\\\\nThis does not apply to most US state and local agencies\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Copyright_status_of_work_by_U.S._subnational_governments], nor to\\\\\\\\ngovernments of other countries!\\\\\\\\nIt is an official governmental item, such as a flag, state emblem, banknote or\\\\\\\\npostage stamp, from a country where such items are exempt from copyright\\\\\\\\naccording to local law.\\\\\\\\nThis does not apply to all countries, nor does it usually apply to all\\\\\\\\npublications! (For instance, it usually doesn't apply to simple publicity\\\\\\\\nphotographs published on a governmental website.) Please look up the copyright\\\\\\\\nrules for the specific country in question. If the country does not have an\\\\\\\\nexemption rule that applies to this item, go on with the section for \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"non-free\\\\\\\\ncopyrighted works\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" below.\\\\\\\\nExplanation:\\\\\\\\nAdd any explanation or evidence necessary to substantiate your statement above.\\\\\\\\nCite and provide a link to the relevant law if possible.It is too simple to be\\\\\\\\neligible for copyright.\\\\\\\\nThis typically applies only to graphics that consist solely of simple geometric\\\\\\\\nshapes and/or a few letters or words, or to items such as mathematical or\\\\\\\\nchemical formulae. It may apply to some very simple logos that do not contain\\\\\\\\ncomplex pictorial elements. It never applies to photographs!\\\\\\\\nIt is in the Public Domain for some other reason.\\\\\\\\nExplanation:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is a copyrighted, non-free work, but I believe it is Fair Use.\\\\\\\\nI have read the Wikipedia rules on Non-Free Content [/wiki/Wikipedia:NFC], and I\\\\\\\\nam prepared to explain how the use of this file will meet the criteria set out\\\\\\\\nthere.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b4/Gtk-dialog-info.svg/20px-Gtk-dialog-info.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nPlease remember that you will need to demonstrate that:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * The file will serve an important function in a particular article; (NFCC8\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Wikipedia:NFCC#8])\\\\\\\\n * It cannot be replaced by any other, free illustration that might yet be\\\\\\\\n   created; (NFCC1 [/wiki/Wikipedia:NFCC#1])\\\\\\\\n * Its use does not negatively affect the commercial interests of its owner\\\\\\\\n   (NFCC2 [/wiki/Wikipedia:NFCC#2])\\\\\\\\n * There will not be more non-free material used than necessary. (NFCC3\\\\\\\\n   [/wiki/Wikipedia:NFCC#3])\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis file will be used in the following article:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEnter the name of exactly one Wikipedia article, without the [[...]] brackets\\\\\\\\nand without the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://en.wikipedia.org/...\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" URL code.\\\\\\\\nIt has to be an actual article, not a talkpage, template, user page, etc.\\\\\\\\nIf you plan to use the file in more than one article, please name only one of\\\\\\\\nthem here. Then, after uploading, open the image description page for editing\\\\\\\\nand add your separate explanations for each additional article manually.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/Gtk-ok.svg/20px-Gtk-ok.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nExample [/wiki/Example]  article okay.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Gtk-dialog-warning.svg/20px-Gtk-dialog-warning.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nThis article doesn't exist!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe article Example [/wiki/Example] could not be found.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease check the spelling, and make sure you enter the name of an existing\\\\\\\\narticle in which you will include this file.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf this is an article you are only planning to write, please write it first and\\\\\\\\nupload the file afterwards.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Gtk-dialog-warning.svg/20px-Gtk-dialog-warning.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nThis is not an actual encyclopedia article!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe page Example [/wiki/Example] is not in the main article namespace. Non-free\\\\\\\\nfiles can only be used in mainspace article pages, not on a user page, talk\\\\\\\\npage, template, etc.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease upload this file only if it is going to be used in an actual article.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf this page is an article draft in your user space, we're sorry, but we must\\\\\\\\nask you to wait until the page is ready and has been moved into mainspace, and\\\\\\\\nonly upload the file after that.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/24/Gtk-dialog-warning.svg/20px-Gtk-dialog-warning.svg.png]\\\\\\\\nThis is a disambiguation page!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThe page Example [/wiki/Example] is not a real article, but a disambiguation\\\\\\\\npage pointing to a number of other pages.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease check and enter the exact title of the actual target article you meant.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNon-free use rationaleThis image is the object of discussion in an article.\\\\\\\\nThis is a copyrighted artwork or photograph, and the image itself is the topic\\\\\\\\nof discussion in the article. The discussion is about the photograph or painting\\\\\\\\nas such, as a creative work, not just about the thing or person it shows.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhich of these options describes this item best?Who created this\\\\\\\\nwork?Author/owner:Date:Source:\\\\\\\\nState exactly where you found this file.\\\\\\\\nFor web sources: please provide a link to the html web page where the file can\\\\\\\\nbe found (\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .html\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"), not a direct link to the image file itself\\\\\\\\n(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"http://... .jpg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\").\\\\\\\\nFor print sources: provide full bibliographic information (author, title,\\\\\\\\npublisher, year, page, etc.)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUsage:The article as a whole is dedicated specifically to a discussion of this\\\\\\\\nparticular photograph/painting. (It is not just about the person or thing shown\\\\\\\\nin the picture.)There is a substantial amount of encyclopedic discussion of this\\\\\\\\nparticular photograph/painting (not just about the person or thing shown in it)\\\\\\\\nin this article. The\\\\\\\\narticle contains a discussion of that work which requires illustration. The\\\\\\\\nphotograph as such is free, or was provided by the creator of the sculpture.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhich of these options describes this item best?First describe who created the\\\\\\\\noriginal work depicted:Creator:Date:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUsage:The article as a whole is dedicated specifically to this work.There is a\\\\\\\\nsubstantial amount of encyclopedic discussion of this work in this article. If\\\\\\\\nyou plan to use the file for any purpose other than this, please do not use this\\\\\\\\nsection, but the one labelled \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"other type of non-free work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" below.Please explain\\\\\\\\nwhy a free alternative to this image cannot be found.\\\\\\\\nFor subjects who died recently: have you made a reasonable effort to find people\\\\\\\\nwho might possess photographs of this person and might be willing to release\\\\\\\\none?\\\\\\\\nFor subjects who lived in the early-to-mid 20th century: have you considered if\\\\\\\\nthere might be an older photograph that has fallen in the public domain?Please\\\\\\\\nexplain why you are confident that our use of the file will not harm any\\\\\\\\ncommercial opportunities of its owner.\\\\\\\\nWe will typically not use a file if its owner has a potential commercial\\\\\\\\ninterest in its use, and if our use of it would compete with its original market\\\\\\\\nrole.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is some other kind of non-free work that I believe is legitimate Fair Use.\\\\\\\\nThis is a copyrighted work whose use does not fall into any of the classes\\\\\\\\nabove. I have read the Wikipedia rules on Non-free content\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Wikipedia:Non-free_content], and I will explain how this file meets all\\\\\\\\nof the criteria set out there.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWhich of these options describes this item best?Author:\\\\\\\\n(Who made this image?)Original\\\\\\\\npublication:\\\\\\\\n(Where, when and how was this image first published?)Date of\\\\\\\\npublication:Source:\\\\\\\\n(Where exactly did you get this file from?)Please explain what exact purpose\\\\\\\\nthis file will serve in the article.\\\\\\\\nPlease be concrete and specific. Don't just copy boilerplate statements from\\\\\\\\nelsewhere. State clearly, in your own words, what this particular file will be\\\\\\\\ndoing in this particular article. Your explanation must make it clear why the\\\\\\\\narticle would be significantly worse off without this file.Please explain why\\\\\\\\nthis purpose could not be served by text alone.Please explain why this purpose\\\\\\\\ncould not be served with an alternative, free illustration that could yet be\\\\\\\\nfound or created.\\\\\\\\nFor a file to be deemed replaceable, it is not necessary that a suitable\\\\\\\\nreplacement already exists. Even if it is merely possible that a replacement\\\\\\\\ncould be created, we will not use the non-free file.Please explain why you are\\\\\\\\nconfident that our use of the file will not harm any commercial opportunities of\\\\\\\\nits owner.\\\\\\\\nWe will typically not use a file if its owner has a potential commercial\\\\\\\\ninterest in its use, and if our use of it would compete with its original market\\\\\\\\nrole.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nRemember that the use of non-free files must be minimal. This can mean several\\\\\\\\nthings:\\\\\\\\n * Don't use more files per article/topic than necessary\\\\\\\\n * Don't use the same file in more articles than necessary\\\\\\\\n * Don't use larger excerpts of a single work than necessary\\\\\\\\n * Don't use images of higher resolution than necessary\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn view of this, please explain how the use of this file will be minimal.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nSpecial source and license conditions (optional)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nAny further relevant information about this file?\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nEdit summary:\\\\\\\\nA brief description of why you are overwriting this file. This will not be saved\\\\\\\\non the description page, but will be shown in its edit history.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYes, I want this file to be immediately available in all Wikimedia projects, in\\\\\\\\nall languages. I will upload it on the Wikimedia Commons.\\\\\\\\nClicking this button will redirect you to a page on Commons. This will only work\\\\\\\\nif you are already logged in there, which is likely the case if you have a\\\\\\\\nunified account [/wiki/Wikipedia:SUL]. Check here\\\\\\\\n[https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:UserLogin] to see if you are logged\\\\\\\\nin.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nNo, I want to upload this file locally.\\\\\\\\nThis way it can be used only on the English Wikipedia. We urge you to upload it\\\\\\\\nto the Commons unless there is a very good reason for it to stay local. Often\\\\\\\\nsuch local files are copied to the Commons for use elsewhere and deleted\\\\\\\\nlocally, requiring extra work for other volunteers. If you do not want your file\\\\\\\\nto be copied to Commons and deleted locally, consider adding the {{Keep local\\\\\\\\n[/wiki/Template:Keep_local]}} tag.Reset this form and start over.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis file doesn't fit either of the categories above.\\\\\\\\nThis file doesn't seem to fall into either of the classes above, or I am not\\\\\\\\ncertain what its status is. I found this file somewhere, but I don't really know\\\\\\\\nwho made it or who owns it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nWell, we're very sorry, but if you're not sure about this file's copyright\\\\\\\\nstatus, or if it doesn't fit into any of the groups above, then:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease don't upload it.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nReally, please don't. Even if you think it would make for a great addition to an\\\\\\\\narticle. We really take these copyright rules very seriously on Wikipedia. Note\\\\\\\\nthat media is assumed to be fully-copyrighted unless shown otherwise; the burden\\\\\\\\nis on the uploader.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn particular, please don't upload:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n * any file you simply found on some website, without knowing who its author or\\\\\\\\n   copyright owner is.\\\\\\\\n * any file you found somewhere, even if you have good reason to believe it has\\\\\\\\n   a copyright owner who would not mind us using it, but you don't have an\\\\\\\\n   explicit licensing statement from them.\\\\\\\\n * any file that was released for publicity purposes by its owners but doesn't\\\\\\\\n   have a fully-free license for free re-use for all purposes.\\\\\\\\n * any file credited to a commercial image agency, such as Reuters, AP or Getty\\\\\\\\n   Images. Such files normally cannot be used even under the \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"Fair Use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" rules,\\\\\\\\n   except in rare cases.\\\\\\\\n * any file that is licensed for use exclusively on Wikipedia, or is free except\\\\\\\\n   that the free license excludes commercial use.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you are in any doubt, please ask some experienced editors for advice before\\\\\\\\nuploading. People will be happy to assist you at Wikipedia:Media copyright\\\\\\\\nquestions [/wiki/Wikipedia:Media_copyright_questions]. Thank you.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPREVIEW (TEST)\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis is the data that will be submitted to upload:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFilename:Edit summary:Text:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nUPLOAD IN PROCESS\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYour file is being uploaded.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nThis might take a minute or two, depending on the size of the file and the speed\\\\\\\\nof your internet connection.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nOnce uploading is completed, you will find your new file at this link:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFile:Example.jpg [/wiki/File:Example.jpg]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFILE SUCCESSFULLY UPLOADED\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n[//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a9/Example.jpg]/wiki/File:Example.jpg\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nYour file has been uploaded successfully and can now be found here:\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nFile:Example.jpg [/wiki/File:Example.jpg]\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPlease follow the link and check that the image description page has all the\\\\\\\\ninformation you meant to include.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIf you want to change the description, just go to the image page, click the\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"edit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" tab at the top of the page and edit just as you would edit any other\\\\\\\\npage.
